<section id="acknowledgement">
    <h2>Statement of Acknowledgement</h2>
    <p>We acknowledge the historical and systemic barriers faced by African American males in education and society at large. This research is dedicated to addressing these challenges and fostering opportunities for equity and success.</p>
</section>

<section id="introduction">
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>This website explores why African American males often disengage from academic programs designed to promote success and how educational practices can be reformed to foster their engagement and achievement.</p>
</section>

<section id="history">
    <h2>Brief Historical Overview</h2>
    <p>The educational journey of African American males has been shaped by a legacy of systemic racism and segregation. Despite legal advancements, disparities in access, support, and resources persist.</p>
</section>

<section id="current-state">
    <h2>Current State of the Issue</h2>
    <p>Today, African American males continue to face lower graduation rates, fewer advanced placement opportunities, and limited representation in academic enrichment programs.</p>
</section>

<section id="impact">
    <h2>Anticipated Impact</h2>
    <p>This research aims to highlight successful strategies and reforms that can enhance educational outcomes for African American males, positively influencing broader societal equity.</p>
</section>

<section id="background">
    <h2>Background</h2>
    <p>Educational reforms must consider both individual and systemic factors that hinder engagement, including socioeconomic challenges, implicit biases, and school discipline practices.</p>
</section>

<section id="research">
    <h2>Research</h2>
    <h3>Problem Statement</h3>
    <p>Despite efforts to improve inclusivity, African American males remain underrepresented in academic success metrics.</p>

    <h3>Purpose Statement</h3>
    <p>The purpose of this research is to identify and implement effective educational practices that promote engagement and success among African American males.</p>

    <h3>Research Questions</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>What barriers prevent African American males from engaging in academic programs?</li>
        <li>How can educational practices be reformed to address these barriers?</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section id="literature">
    <h2>Literature Review: Major Themes and Gaps</h2>
    <p>Key themes include mentorship, culturally responsive teaching, and family engagement. Gaps exist in longitudinal studies addressing systemic reforms.</p>
    <p><a href="#" style="color: blue;">View Mind Map</a></p>
</section>

